      "weather": "FINE",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to put the pen through any of these. BUNKER HUT (4) makes the most appeal on the back of strong NSW form this prep. Handy all the way when beaten under two lengths in the BM94 Bert Lillye Memorial at Kembla last start. Drops 3kgs with the claim and should be close to his peak at the third run back. ABOUT TO EXPLODE (1) started $1.75 and got the job done in a BM85 over this course and distance a fortnight ago. More depth to this and he goes up 2kgs but his record here at 1200m is impressive. RESTONICA (3) had never won when fresh from a spell until five weeks ago in a BM78 here at today's journey. Kept fresh and his second-up form is far better. Lightly raced five-year-old who might be back better than ever. Genuine mare PARTY SPIRIT (8) is in the mix with just 53kgs after the claim.",
